00:37:52,150 --> 00:37:53,690
Who is this young maiden?

520
00:37:55,940 --> 00:37:57,820
How beautiful.

521
00:38:00,110 --> 00:38:02,030
-How old are you?
-25.

522
00:38:02,700 --> 00:38:04,660
-Are you married?
-I want to.

523
00:38:06,280 --> 00:38:08,540
Oh no, at that age?

524
00:38:08,620 --> 00:38:09,870
Do you have a plan?

525
00:38:10,080 --> 00:38:13,380
You should be having many babies by now.

526
00:38:14,130 --> 00:38:17,130
There's no worse disrespect than this
to your parents.

527
00:38:22,800 --> 00:38:24,090
It's raining, Grandma.

528
00:38:25,260 --> 00:38:28,140
Please get some rest while
watching the rain fall.

529
00:38:29,020 --> 00:38:33,150
Sewing seems to have
absolutely no positive effect on dementia.

530
00:38:58,710 --> 00:39:00,460
It's me instead of grandma today.

531
00:39:03,630 --> 00:39:04,630
Let's go.

532
00:39:08,470 --> 00:39:10,310
I don't think it'll stop today.

533
00:39:22,280 --> 00:39:23,280
Let's go.

534
00:40:57,790 --> 00:40:58,960
Wait up.

535
00:41:00,000 --> 00:41:02,000
What's wrong?
Did something happen?

536
00:41:07,090 --> 00:41:08,430
Your friend's grandmother?

537
00:41:11,510 --> 00:41:12,510
Is it…

538
00:41:14,640 --> 00:41:15,720
the umbrella grandma--

539
00:41:20,150 --> 00:41:22,110
That's why you even changed shifts.

540
00:41:38,580 --> 00:41:43,000
EONJU UNIVERSITY HOSPITAL
FUNERAL HOME

541
00:41:56,220 --> 00:41:58,600
-Should we go that way instead?
-Why?

542
00:42:09,190 --> 00:42:11,200
-That's him, isn't it?
-Who?

543
00:42:11,910 --> 00:42:15,200
-Is that him?
-That's…

544
00:42:15,780 --> 00:42:16,790
Kim Tae-hee.

545
00:42:22,170 --> 00:42:24,830
That's right.
It's Dr. Kim Tae-hee.

546
00:42:36,970 --> 00:42:37,970
<i>Baby.</i>

547
00:42:39,060 --> 00:42:42,310
<i>I know it's painful and hard.</i>

548
00:42:42,600 --> 00:42:45,230
It is for me too.
I'm about to lose my mind.

549
00:42:46,360 --> 00:42:49,780
But why do we have to break up
because of this? Why?

550
00:42:51,150 --> 00:42:53,700
I'll wait as long as you need it.

551
00:42:54,110 --> 00:42:56,830
You'll be okay after some time.

552
00:42:58,990 --> 00:43:00,000
Chung-ha.

553
00:43:10,630 --> 00:43:12,340
I just can't stand myself.

554
00:43:13,680 --> 00:43:15,970
Me, being alive and breathing

555
00:43:22,850 --> 00:43:24,270
I'm disgusted by myself.

556
00:43:30,110 --> 00:43:33,490
Struggling to form a family with you,

557
00:43:34,320 --> 00:43:35,950
even this rain falling on me,

558
00:43:41,240 --> 00:43:42,580
it's just all horrible.

559
00:43:50,210 --> 00:43:51,210
I'm sorry.

560
00:44:04,600 --> 00:44:06,980
TAE-HEE

561
00:44:22,910 --> 00:44:25,580
So that you don't have
anything to worry about,

562
00:44:26,620 --> 00:44:28,750
we will take great care of everything.

563
00:44:29,710 --> 00:44:33,000
As you are also a friend of our employee,

564
00:44:34,210 --> 00:44:36,630
we will be even more attentive.

565
00:44:37,340 --> 00:44:39,680
Thank you. We will leave it to you.

566
00:44:42,220 --> 00:44:43,220
How amazing.

567
00:44:43,850 --> 00:44:44,850
Dong-joo.

568
00:44:46,020 --> 00:44:51,770
I have never even imagined that
you would be sending my mother off.

569
00:44:54,320 --> 00:44:56,150
We'll leave her to you.

570
00:44:58,450 --> 00:44:59,450
Yes, sir.

571
00:45:01,700 --> 00:45:02,700
Look after

572
00:45:03,200 --> 00:45:04,580
So-ra for us as well.

573
00:45:05,870 --> 00:45:06,870
I will.

574
00:45:07,210 --> 00:45:08,210
Thank you.

575
00:45:10,630 --> 00:45:11,630
Dong-joo.

576
00:45:12,790 --> 00:45:14,250
Go ahead to your friends.

577
00:45:15,300 --> 00:45:16,300
Yes, go ahead.

578
00:45:29,560 --> 00:45:32,060
What I regret the most is

579
00:45:33,980 --> 00:45:34,980
every day

580
00:45:36,570 --> 00:45:37,570
"Grandma,

581
00:45:38,740 --> 00:45:39,950
who am I?"

582
00:45:41,240 --> 00:45:42,740
I would ask her.

583
00:45:43,870 --> 00:45:45,450
Trying to make sure

584
00:45:47,080 --> 00:45:48,790
that she hasn't forgotten me.

585
00:45:51,670 --> 00:45:55,630
Grandma struggled so hard every time.

586
00:45:58,510 --> 00:46:01,090
What was so important
for her to recognize me

587
00:46:04,640 --> 00:46:08,180
that I asked over and over again,
and eventually get disappointed?

588
00:46:12,600 --> 00:46:13,770
I should have just said

589
00:46:14,150 --> 00:46:15,150
"Grandma,

590
00:46:16,480 --> 00:46:18,610
it's okay to forget everything."

591
00:46:19,820 --> 00:46:20,820
I should have.

592
00:46:21,740 --> 00:46:25,700
She even forgot about Dad who she loved
more than her own life.

593
00:46:27,200 --> 00:46:29,790
She erased off yesterday,

594
00:46:31,290 --> 00:46:33,960
and always only had today.

595
00:46:34,830 --> 00:46:37,050
What was so important about that?

596
00:46:41,300 --> 00:46:43,970
They say they take
all of the good memories.

597
00:46:44,840 --> 00:46:46,470
She will remember everything.

598
00:46:50,600 --> 00:46:51,770
Did you have

599
00:46:52,890 --> 00:46:53,900
anything you

600
00:46:54,850 --> 00:46:56,560
wanted to do for Grandma?

601
00:46:56,810 --> 00:46:57,940
Yesterday,

602
00:47:00,990 --> 00:47:02,490
Grandma asked me

603
00:47:04,160 --> 00:47:07,280
to clip her nails,

604
00:47:08,790 --> 00:47:11,700
and I wasn't able to.

605
00:47:16,580 --> 00:47:19,090
Hey! Bring another bottle of <i>Soju </i>here!

606
00:47:19,170 --> 00:47:21,010
-Right away.
-What in the world…

607
00:47:24,590 --> 00:47:25,590
Hey, lady.

608
00:47:27,600 --> 00:47:28,890
What is wrong with him?

609
00:47:29,850 --> 00:47:31,930
Who is that old guy?

610
00:47:32,480 --> 00:47:35,140
I don't know. I guess Grandma knew him.

611
00:47:36,230 --> 00:47:37,230
So annoying.

612
00:48:02,800 --> 00:48:04,380
You did well today as always.

613
00:48:08,550 --> 00:48:09,720
It's tomorrow, right?

614
00:48:10,810 --> 00:48:11,810
The Coffining.

615
00:48:16,770 --> 00:48:17,770
Yes.

616
00:48:19,480 --> 00:48:20,980
So that you don't regret anything

617
00:48:25,530 --> 00:48:27,910
Everything you wanted to say

618
00:48:28,110 --> 00:48:29,320
or couldn't say,

619
00:48:30,950 --> 00:48:32,830
you should go tell her.

620
00:48:37,710 --> 00:48:38,880
She would be happy…

621
00:48:42,840 --> 00:48:44,170
that until the very end

622
00:48:45,630 --> 00:48:47,220
you were with her.

623
00:49:26,800 --> 00:49:27,840
My little pumpkin.

624
00:49:29,010 --> 00:49:30,930
When did you grow up so much?

625
00:49:38,180 --> 00:49:40,020
Please don't leave, Grandma.

626
00:49:41,850 --> 00:49:43,560
How can I not?

627
00:49:44,650 --> 00:49:46,690
I'm blessed with you on my way.

628
00:49:49,070 --> 00:49:51,280
I got to see you, Dong-joo.

629
00:49:54,240 --> 00:49:55,280
Dong-joo.

630
00:49:56,540 --> 00:50:01,540
Thank you for taking good care
of this old grandma for this long.

631
00:50:06,340 --> 00:50:07,460
So-ra has

632
00:50:08,300 --> 00:50:10,840
also worked hard taking care of me.

633
00:50:12,590 --> 00:50:16,890
How hard it must have been for her,
taking care of a broken grandma.

634
00:50:17,680 --> 00:50:21,980
I should have left earlier so
my kids didn't have to struggle so much.

635
00:50:23,810 --> 00:50:25,060
Though a part of me

636
00:50:25,730 --> 00:50:28,690
wanted to go after I saw her get married.

637
00:50:30,740 --> 00:50:33,660
To give So-ra as a wedding gift,

638
00:50:33,950 --> 00:50:37,030
I prepared something with my bad skills.

639
00:50:37,790 --> 00:50:41,870
My brain had become a rock
and I couldn't tell her.

640
00:50:42,750 --> 00:50:47,210
You can tell So-ra to make sure
she takes it when she gets married, right?

641
00:50:48,340 --> 00:50:49,340
Of course.

642
00:50:54,260 --> 00:50:58,560
If I had a little more time,
I would have prepared one more.

643
00:51:00,060 --> 00:51:03,020
I'm sorry.

644
00:51:04,230 --> 00:51:07,520
No, I'm sorry.

645
00:51:08,940 --> 00:51:10,030
And…

646
00:51:12,280 --> 00:51:17,160
thank you so much for not taking
pity on me because I had no mother.

647
00:51:18,200 --> 00:51:22,330
For being compassionate and loving to me.

648
00:51:24,620 --> 00:51:31,090
Yes. I'll tell your mother
when I meet her.

649
00:51:31,630 --> 00:51:36,930
I promise I'll tell her that
Dong-joo grew up beautiful and great.

650
00:51:37,010 --> 00:51:38,010
Thank you.

651
00:51:38,350 --> 00:51:42,230
Of course, I'm sure mom is
always watching over you.

652
00:51:46,150 --> 00:51:48,900
Stop the crying, child.

653
00:51:51,110 --> 00:51:56,910
Grandma is happy.
Happy that I got to see you before I go.

654
00:51:57,570 --> 00:52:01,790
Happy that I can talk to you
with a clear mind like this.

655
00:52:06,330 --> 00:52:09,170
So-ra also, but Dong-joo,

656
00:52:09,750 --> 00:52:12,130
find your match quickly.

657
00:52:14,800 --> 00:52:17,340
Love is an amazing feeling.

658
00:52:18,550 --> 00:52:21,600
There's nothing
more precious than that in this world.

659
00:52:22,220 --> 00:52:23,890
When it's hard and tiring,

660
00:52:24,560 --> 00:52:29,190
you remember those memories to endure
for the rest of your life.

661
00:52:30,190 --> 00:52:34,530
The times I waited for So-ra's grandpa,
keeping the cooked rice warm.

662
00:52:36,450 --> 00:52:38,410
Going past the town entrance

663
00:52:39,320 --> 00:52:42,830
to greet So-ra's grandpa
coming home on a bicycle.

664
00:52:44,540 --> 00:52:47,210
When he would pull out
roasted chestnuts from his clothes

665
00:52:47,620 --> 00:52:51,170
that he kept in there just in case
it gets cold on the 10 <i>ri </i>way home.

666
00:52:52,630 --> 00:52:55,380
When we would eat them together.

667
00:52:57,430 --> 00:53:00,510
You live thanks to those tiny moments.

668
00:53:02,220 --> 00:53:04,640
Those memories will never, ever

669
00:53:05,220 --> 00:53:06,350
be forgotten

670
00:53:07,230 --> 00:53:09,150
or disappear.

671
00:53:12,940 --> 00:53:16,110
Whether it rains or pours,

672
00:53:17,110 --> 00:53:19,490
live your life loving.

673
00:53:21,280 --> 00:53:22,280
Yes, ma'am.

674
00:53:23,200 --> 00:53:27,120
Soon, there will be a day
you recognize him.

675
00:53:30,080 --> 00:53:33,290
That miraculous moment will come to you.

676
00:53:35,920 --> 00:53:36,920
Alright.

677
00:53:49,560 --> 00:53:50,980
Grandma…

678
00:54:07,910 --> 00:54:10,670
COFFIN ROOM
VIEWING ROOM

679
00:54:24,470 --> 00:54:26,640
Grandma looked pretty.

680
00:54:27,640 --> 00:54:28,640
What.

681
00:54:30,940 --> 00:54:32,230
Thanks.

682
00:54:35,520 --> 00:54:37,020
You're so amazing.

683
00:54:45,830 --> 00:54:48,830
Why are you crying more than me?

684
00:54:59,010 --> 00:55:02,050
-So-ra's mom, come out here.
-Yes.

685
00:55:04,890 --> 00:55:08,010
Hey, girl! Get me some more of this.

686
00:55:10,140 --> 00:55:11,480
<i>Ajeossi, </i>please leave.

687
00:55:11,560 --> 00:55:13,940
-What?
-Please leave.

688
00:55:14,020 --> 00:55:16,020
How many bottles did he have in two days?

689
00:55:18,270 --> 00:55:20,150
You disrespectful bitch!

690
00:55:20,230 --> 00:55:22,990
How dare you talk back to an adul--

691
00:55:23,530 --> 00:55:24,820
Sir.

692
00:55:26,160 --> 00:55:28,910
Sir, you must have had a lot to drink.

693
00:55:29,700 --> 00:55:31,000
Who the hell are you?

694
00:55:34,080 --> 00:55:36,380
The departure is
early morning tomorrow, and

695
00:55:36,710 --> 00:55:40,800
the bereaved are cleaning up
and going home, so you should also go--

696
00:55:43,630 --> 00:55:45,510
Sir, you shouldn't be doing this--

697
00:55:49,100 --> 00:55:50,180
Sir!

698
00:55:50,430 --> 00:55:53,680
-Should we go outside and have a smoke?
-Yeah?

699
00:55:55,270 --> 00:55:57,400
Let us go then.

700
00:55:57,650 --> 00:55:58,650
Let go of me!

701
00:56:00,730 --> 00:56:01,730
Sir, your shoes.

702
00:56:01,820 --> 00:56:03,570
Cigarette. Give me cigarette.

703
00:56:03,780 --> 00:56:05,530
Where's my cigarette?!

704
00:56:07,620 --> 00:56:09,660
Let go of me!

705
00:56:10,790 --> 00:56:13,000
Hey. Who do you think you are?

706
00:56:15,000 --> 00:56:19,000
Let go. Let go!

707
00:56:20,710 --> 00:56:21,710
Leave.

708
00:56:25,630 --> 00:56:26,630
Leave, I said.

709
00:56:29,640 --> 00:56:30,640
Dad.

710
00:56:31,010 --> 00:56:32,720
What do you think about that guy?

711
00:56:33,720 --> 00:56:35,270
I'm fond of him.

712
00:56:36,560 --> 00:56:37,560
Me too.

713
00:56:38,400 --> 00:56:40,650
Did Grandma send him to me?

714
00:56:42,650 --> 00:56:43,900
Why would she?

715
00:56:46,700 --> 00:56:48,110
-Hm?
-Yeah.

716
00:56:51,660 --> 00:56:52,660
Director.

717
00:56:54,620 --> 00:56:57,210
Dong-joo. Thank you so much.

718
00:56:58,290 --> 00:57:00,880
-It's nothing.
-Thank you, very much.

719
00:57:03,960 --> 00:57:06,050
Thank you. We'll see you around.

720
00:57:16,520 --> 00:57:17,520
Thank you.

721
00:57:25,690 --> 00:57:27,530
By the way, Dong-joo.

722
00:57:29,240 --> 00:57:31,030
I think Grandma

723
00:57:32,450 --> 00:57:34,790
left me a gift.

724
00:57:37,290 --> 00:57:38,960
I just feel that way.

725
00:57:41,830 --> 00:57:43,000
You saw the gift?

726
00:57:46,170 --> 00:57:47,170
Already?

727
00:57:49,220 --> 00:57:50,220
Huh?

728
00:58:05,360 --> 00:58:07,320
<i>Who would use this kind of blanket?</i>

729
00:58:17,620 --> 00:58:20,540
This is for my granddaughter

730
00:58:21,250 --> 00:58:23,630
when she gets married.

731
00:58:57,200 --> 00:59:00,040
Grandma.

732
00:59:20,140 --> 00:59:23,140
BONGSU CINEMA

733
00:59:35,990 --> 00:59:37,200
I guess it's raining.

734
00:59:38,620 --> 00:59:41,000
Yeah. I guess it's raining again.

735
00:59:43,080 --> 00:59:45,580
Is that why others are late?
Traffic from the rain?

736
00:59:46,130 --> 00:59:48,710
They'll be here.
They said they'd be on time.

737
00:59:52,720 --> 00:59:53,720
Yes, Hae-an<i>.</i>

738
00:59:53,800 --> 00:59:57,390
<i>-Dong-joo, what do I do?</i>
-What happened?

739
00:59:57,760 --> 00:59:59,720
<i>You know the Sokyeong</i>
<i>arcade incident, right?</i>

740
01:00:00,060 --> 01:00:02,350
<i>This has put</i>
<i>the entire department on edge.</i>

741
01:00:02,430 --> 01:00:06,020
<i>They're telling all of us to do rounds.</i>
<i>Man, this sucks.</i>

742
01:00:06,480 --> 01:00:08,230
Oh no. What do we do?

743
01:00:08,310 --> 01:00:11,860
<i>I wanted to share a popcorn and watch</i>
<i>a movie at a multiplex theater with you.</i>

744
01:00:11,940 --> 01:00:15,110
<i>Why did such a terrible crime have to</i>
<i>happen right now?</i>

745
01:00:15,360 --> 01:00:16,660
<i>This really sucks.</i>

746
01:00:17,320 --> 01:00:18,870
That's too bad.

747
01:00:19,740 --> 01:00:21,450
Good luck. Bye.

748
01:00:24,160 --> 01:00:25,540
<i>I don't think I can go.</i>

749
01:00:25,620 --> 01:00:29,460
-Hae-an <i>ssi </i>says he can't make it.
-Neither can my uncle.

750
01:00:34,170 --> 01:00:35,630
Then, we should leave too, right?

751
01:00:37,590 --> 01:00:40,220
-Should we just watch it? The two of us?
-Huh?

752
01:00:40,430 --> 01:00:44,770
-This is almost like we got ditched.
-It's whatever.

753
01:00:46,230 --> 01:00:47,730
How about we do rock, paper, scissors?

754
01:00:49,190 --> 01:00:53,480
-Do what the winner says.
-You want to watch the movie that bad?

755
01:00:54,820 --> 01:00:56,200
-No.
-Then why?

756
01:00:58,490 --> 01:01:01,700
It would be nice to say
we <i>chose </i>to go home.

757
01:01:04,660 --> 01:01:09,290
Did you come here because you had
nothing to do? You made the time.

758
01:01:10,080 --> 01:01:13,500
It sucks to just go home like this.
It's nice to feel good at least.

759
01:01:17,170 --> 01:01:18,180
Okay, then.

760
01:01:19,180 --> 01:01:20,720
-I'm gonna do rock.
-Huh?

761
01:01:21,140 --> 01:01:23,560
Dong-joo <i>ssi, </i>you choose
however you want.

762
01:01:27,140 --> 01:01:28,350
Rock, paper, scissors!

763
01:01:29,690 --> 01:01:30,690
What?

764
01:01:30,980 --> 01:01:32,770
-We're watching the movie.
-wha--

765
01:01:33,270 --> 01:01:34,270
What I want.

766
01:01:35,400 --> 01:01:36,610
I had some free time.

767
01:01:42,660 --> 01:01:43,660
C'mon, let's go.

768
01:01:52,170 --> 01:01:53,460
It's been a while.

769
01:02:01,510 --> 01:02:03,970
Wow, it's been a while,
but they're all going in.

770
01:02:06,220 --> 01:02:07,220
How is it for you?

771
01:02:09,230 --> 01:02:12,310
Don't throw with both hands.
Left hand only holds, with a snap.

772
01:02:13,440 --> 01:02:15,690
Like this.

773
01:02:23,070 --> 01:02:24,240
I won't go easy.

774
01:02:27,450 --> 01:02:28,790
I better defend.

775
01:02:40,340 --> 01:02:41,340
Just you wait.

776
01:02:49,180 --> 01:02:53,480
Please.

777
01:02:55,690 --> 01:02:57,480
I did it!

778
01:03:00,190 --> 01:03:01,200
Did you see that?

779
01:03:02,150 --> 01:03:05,120
Amazing!
A stuffie worth 58000 Won!

780
01:03:14,420 --> 01:03:16,290
-You're giving it to me?
-Yeah.

781
01:03:53,960 --> 01:03:56,250
<i>-Did you go to the movies?</i>
-I didn't go.

782
01:03:56,830 --> 01:03:58,790
<i>Why? Why didn't you go?</i>

783
01:04:00,050 --> 01:04:03,340
<i>You took the whole day off</i>
<i>to go with the girl next door.</i>

784
01:04:03,800 --> 01:04:06,260
<i>You had an earful from</i>
<i>the station chief too.</i>

785
01:04:07,010 --> 01:04:08,010
Just because.

786
01:04:10,390 --> 01:04:11,520
It's raining.

787
01:04:14,520 --> 01:04:17,520
BONGSU CINEMA

788
01:04:37,540 --> 01:04:39,670
Give me a minute.
I'll go get an umbrella.

789
01:04:40,130 --> 01:04:41,130
Wait.

790
01:04:43,920 --> 01:04:44,920
What's up?

791
01:04:53,520 --> 01:04:54,520
Dong-joo!

792
01:05:41,560 --> 01:05:42,560
Really?

793
01:05:50,950 --> 01:05:53,780
There's no quiet day
with Baek Dong-joo.

794
01:05:54,830 --> 01:05:57,410
I was scared for no reason.
It's just nice and cool.

795
01:05:57,500 --> 01:05:58,500
Huh?

796
01:05:59,500 --> 01:06:00,500
The rain.

797
01:06:03,380 --> 01:06:04,710
Every time it rained,

798
01:06:05,050 --> 01:06:07,630
I always just waited for it to stop,

799
01:06:08,220 --> 01:06:10,970
or waited for someone
to bring me an umbrella.

800
01:06:11,890 --> 01:06:13,010
I didn't have to.

801
01:06:13,510 --> 01:06:16,180
You just found out? At age 25?

802
01:06:19,690 --> 01:06:23,770
Ever since I started the job,
I never thought to myself I was lonely.

803
01:06:25,400 --> 01:06:26,400
Well,

804
01:06:27,650 --> 01:06:31,990
I was about to for the first time,

805
01:06:36,370 --> 01:06:38,750
but then someone told me
not to chicken out.

806
01:06:54,340 --> 01:06:55,760
Your eyes are all puffy.

807
01:07:02,560 --> 01:07:04,810
It's nice out here today.

808
01:07:06,020 --> 01:07:07,020
Just today?

809
01:07:08,230 --> 01:07:10,150
Didn't you say you like rain?

810
01:07:11,820 --> 01:07:12,820
It's a lie.

811
01:07:13,660 --> 01:07:16,410
-Why would you lie about that?
-I wonder about that too.

812
01:07:17,950 --> 01:07:19,660
I said something meaningless.

813
01:07:24,620 --> 01:07:26,960
With that being said, it's raining,

814
01:07:28,170 --> 01:07:29,170
so <i>Haemulpajeon?</i>

815
01:07:32,590 --> 01:07:33,680
With <i>makgeolli?</i>

816
01:07:34,930 --> 01:07:36,010
Sounds good.

817
01:07:38,430 --> 01:07:39,430
Kim Tae-hee.

818
01:08:31,270 --> 01:08:32,690
<i>Have you thought about me?</i>

819
01:08:32,780 --> 01:08:34,190
<i>I want to move, too.</i>

820
01:08:34,280 --> 01:08:35,360
<i>Do you guys know?</i>

821
01:08:35,610 --> 01:08:37,740
<i>Feeling concerned about someone.</i>

822
01:08:37,820 --> 01:08:38,820
<i>First love?</i>

823
01:08:39,030 --> 01:08:40,030
<i>Yes.</i>

824
01:08:40,780 --> 01:08:42,790
<i>-First love.</i>
<i>-Why are you lying?</i>

825
01:08:43,250 --> 01:08:44,250
<i>It's true though.</i>

826
01:08:44,330 --> 01:08:46,250
<i>-I'll get off here.</i>
<i>-Here?</i>
